Package org.universAAL.ontology.hvac

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Air_Conditioning
    Class for All Air Conditioning systems.
    Air_Conditioning_Mode
    Air_Conditioning_Mode is a type of mode only for Air_Conditioning in which user can find three modes.
    Heating
    Class for Heating systems.
    Heating_Mode
    A type of mode only for Heating in which user can find three modes.
    Hvac
    HVAC stands for Heather,Ventilation and Air Conditioning, in this class are defined the different properties that can find in any Hvac system.
    HvacOntology
    HVAC (Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning Ontology.
    Mode
    Superclass for the different modes of HVAC, include Air_Conditioning_Mode, Heating_Mode and Ventilation_Mode.
    Target_Temperature
    A type of HVAC device that is capable of reading the temperature and react according to a target temperature.
    Ventilation
    Class for all Ventilation systems.
    Ventilation_Mode
    A type of HVAC mode only for Ventilation systems in which user can find three modes: Fan its a mode in which the user sets the ventilation mode is On, also in many hvac system this mode is known as "Fan Mode". Dry enables dehumidifier technology.
